          <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-4">7. Removing the App</h2>
          <div class="h-1 w-12 rounded-full bg-gradient-to-r from-accent to-accent-tertiary mb-6"></div>
          <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-6">
            To uninstall the Toastmasters app from your Zoom account:
          </p>

          <div class="space-y-6">
            <div class="flex gap-4">
              <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-red-500/20 text-red-400 flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-sm">1</div>
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-text-primary font-semibold mb-1">Open Zoom Settings</h4>
                <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">
                  Log in to your Zoom account at <a href="https://zoom.us" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-secondary transition-colors">zoom.us</a> and navigate to <strong class="text-text-primary">Settings</strong>.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="flex gap-4">
              <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-red-500/20 text-red-400 flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-sm">2</div>
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-text-primary font-semibold mb-1">Go to Apps</h4>
                <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">
                  Click on the <strong class="text-text-primary">Apps</strong> section in the left sidebar, then select <strong class="text-text-primary">Installed Apps</strong> (or <strong class="text-text-primary">Added Apps</strong>).
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="flex gap-4">
              <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-red-500/20 text-red-400 flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-sm">3</div>
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-text-primary font-semibold mb-1">Find & Remove</h4>
                <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">
                  Find <strong class="text-text-primary">Toastmasters</strong> in the list and click <strong class="text-text-primary">Remove</strong> or <strong class="text-text-primary">Uninstall</strong>.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="flex gap-4">
              <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-red-500/20 text-red-400 flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-sm">4</div>
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-text-primary font-semibold mb-1">Confirm Removal</h4>
                <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">
                  Confirm the removal when prompted. The app and its authorization will be revoked immediately.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-xl p-5 mt-6">
            <h4 class="text-text-primary font-semibold mb-2">What happens to your data?</h4>
            <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">
              The Toastmasters app uses a <strong class="text-text-primary">fully ephemeral design</strong>. No personal data is stored permanently. Meeting state exists only during the active session and is automatically deleted within 4 hours. Once you remove the app, no data remains on our servers.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- 8. Troubleshooting -->
        <div id="troubleshooting" class="fade-in-up scroll-mt-24">
          <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-4">8. Troubleshooting</h2>
          <div class="h-1 w-12 rounded-full bg-gradient-to-r from-accent to-accent-tertiary mb-6"></div>

          <div class="space-y-6">
            <div class="bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-xl p-5">
              <h4 class="text-text-primary font-semibold mb-2">App shows "Connecting to Zoom..."</h4>
              <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm">
                This means the app is initializing the Zoom SDK. Wait a few seconds. If it persists, close and reopen the app from the Apps tab. Ensure you're using the latest version of the Zoom desktop client.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-xl p-5">
              <h4 class="text-text-primary font-semibold mb-2">Guests see "Waiting for host..."</h4>
              <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm">
                This is normal. The host must click "Start Meeting" in the app before guests can see the meeting dashboard. Ask your meeting host to start the meeting in the app.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-xl p-5">
              <h4 class="text-text-primary font-semibold mb-2">Participant names not appearing in dropdowns</h4>
              <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm">
                The app pulls participant names from the Zoom meeting context. Make sure participants have joined the meeting (not just the waiting room). Try closing and reopening the app.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-xl p-5">
              <h4 class="text-text-primary font-semibold mb-2">State not syncing for guests</h4>
              <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm">
                Guest state updates every 2 seconds. If updates seem stale, close the app sidebar and reopen it. Ensure you have a stable internet connection.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-xl p-5">
              <h4 class="text-text-primary font-semibold mb-2">Word of the Day not fetching</h4>
              <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm">
                The word is fetched from external dictionary APIs. If the fetch fails, try again or manually enter a word. This can happen due to temporary API rate limits.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

